                                                                                                                                     NATION BRIEFS
                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram, Jan. 20 (PTI): Singer K.J. Yesudas has claimed he was turned out of a Kerala temple after being invited there, sparking another row in a state where he has been shut out of shrines on religious grounds.
     
	Yesudas, a Christian who has belted out hundreds of Hindu devotional songs, said the treatment meted out to him at Kadampuzha Devi Temple had deeply pained him.
         
	 New Delhi (PTI): The use of e-cards has fallen this season because of high congestion and virus threats. Greeting cards are a better form of expressing emotions. Technology has expanded the ways people connected but has not replaced the use of these cards, a Hallmark Cards spokesperson said.
         
	New Delhi (PTI): Indian Railways will introduce environment- friendly toilets in all passenger coaches. Some will discharge the waste only after a train leaves a station and some others only into specialised tanks at terminuses. Some will use bacteria to degrade the waste and turn it odourless.
         
	Lakhimpur Kheri (PTI): A woman teacher was found murdered at her home in Uttar Pradeshs Lakhimpur Kheri on Sunday. Uma Singhals bloodstained body was discovered by her maid.
                                                            
